data.title: Postgraduate Education
data.meta_description:
rouse_ball - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. The document provides information about the Rouse Ball Professorship of Mathematics position at the University of Cambridge's Department of Pure Mathematics and Mathematical Statistics. The 3-sentence summary is:

The Rouse Ball Professorship of Mathematics is a leading position established in 1927 at the University of Cambridge's Department of Pure Mathematics and Mathematical Statistics, seeking an individual with an outstanding research record and vision to build on strengths in research. Key responsibilities include teaching, research, examining, supervision, and administration. Candidates must have a PhD and demonstrate abilities in research, leadership, attracting funding, academic planning, and interacting with staff and students.
